    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah I would agree that the set question is a good question for someone at your level. You should set it up as an <code>Equiv</code>.  To do the application to numbers you should probably find lemmas in the library saying things like \"size of A-&gt;B is b^a\" and \"size of AxB is a*b\" rather than proving them (here a=#A and b=#B)</p>",
        "id": 504650422,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1741628451
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(constructing equivalences like <code>(Fin n → Fin k) ≃ Fin (k^n)</code> is not too hard though and more fun than proving <code>(α × β → γ) ≃ (α → (β → γ))</code>)</p>",
